spanGrp.span: Long time ago, in the land of the Anals..
Alal nahla hinto, va ihnim hlo phalbi thung..
Boys and girls, mostly during winter
hmikowm bowm ungjā...jenu, ataheeng panu̠ ṭu ṭu jenu
they sat by the fireplace, laugh out together
making fire,while sitting by the fireplace
hmi va o nahin thung tuwng
Alal tuwng dajoso, nahla tuwng dajoso,
what was said by the boy or girl
Vaṭa napum bu̠ icha te dāva?
What is it that cries while eating?
Phen: Traditional Cotton Gin (machine to separate cotton from the seeds)
Cotton gin makes the sound "keko keko" (crying)
pala to hepahmom meme hepahmom meme keko
while spining, but it still continues eating the cotton that we put in
vaṭa napum bṵ icha to phen va vada vachung ka
so cotton gin is the thing that cries while eating.
Tangsọ: a small sharp knife with long handle
Meje: a sharp type of grass
Ahmāng ha nahe chọ thung meeje heeng
while entering the forest, sharp "Meje" grass
That "Meje" grass is called forest knife, one said
Forest kitchen knife? He asks again.
pahri sṵwl to navā thung nāthun doh nāthun dohnu̠
thatch grass: long grass used in previous times for making roofs.
Thatch grass poke us when we walk in the forest
Va u̠w diil vin manu vane diil ivin
The elder one doesn't wear pants, but the younger one does.
Ruh eh vadowng thung te vakowng amka
When it is small, it has a shell,
but when it grows larger, the shell just falls off.
That was what he would mean.
Dah oh? Thing kumpalen hnathọ iṭo? Dah va?
What sneezes on a crooked tree trunk? What is it?
Vaheka lol va, amatuwng mi hathọ ṭonu, "thuung"
He shoots the gun, when people sneeze, it goes "boom"
danu amato, Thingkum palen hathọ iṭo dava danite
The thing that sneezes on the crooked tree trunk..
If he says "Gun" "-Ohǃ You are right."
Da oh, jung jung hang hang? danite
What is it that neither goes up nor down?
chahel to "tum tum" ajungnu hangnu ajungnu hangnu
The stick goes up and down, up and down
Dah oh, khamṭung len buvum, buvum halnu iamjā?
What sits on the veranda, wearing a black shawl?
Shajowl akhe: ancient game of indebting someone with one animal butt to be paid later by the loser..or sometimes as a points during the game.
If one replied "-I don't know". (The questioner): "- One animal butt (=one game point).
Hal e to khamṭung lentuwng va e nate vum jānu e am jāva.
Chicken dung lies on the veranda all black in colour.
khamṭung len bu ivum halnu iung jāva.
Just like something that wears a black shawl and sits on the veranda.
Dah oh...Vāpu̠ ṭungka danite, vāhmi ilejā..?
What is it that wags its tail when the owner arrives?
Vi, vāpu̠ ṭungka daki, vāhmi ale dondon ale dondon nu, vi
Dog, As the owner arrives, it keeps on waving its tail.., a dog
Dah oh...in thalkhon thung vāhmi ile jā?
What is it that wags its tail inside or outside the house?
"No idea", one said..The other replied "It's a broom"
chunṭhọ te vāhmi ile ru iṭol athe athe chunṭhọ mi in vavanghruki e
When someone sweeps the floor with a broom, it is like a thing waving a tail.
"A fat person never comes back after he/she was sent to bring something?"
Saphi hmu: traditional Ammo for sling round in shape used for shooting birds and animals, made out of mud..
Sāphito peemnu naheka dohki avangle mi amato vatingnava
When it is shot, as it was round like a fat belly, it would not come back.
What is a smoke that comes out of heaven?
It carries a child both at the back and in the front?
"The thing that carries the child in the head?", if asked.
Mowng.. Mowng to valu̠che ha, vapu va..
Banana, Banana carries the child in its head..
What is it? During the daylight...
What is it? During the daylight...
It is blind (= its eyes are dark)
But when its dark outside, it can see (= its eyes are bright)?
pām to, pām varthungte karii hmira hmira ṭhanra ṭhanmi
During the day it never open its headlights
but it would light up at night.
